OL,5, A Tennessee school board has defended  
OL,6, its ban on a Pulitzer prize-winning    
OL,7, novel about the Holocaust being taught 
OL,8, in its classrooms.                     
OL,10,FFollowing a backlash, board members    
OL,11,Fcited the book's use of swear words,   
OL,12,Fnudity and suicide, saying it was      
OL,13,F"simply too adult-oriented" for pupils.
OL,15,FThe graphic novel Maus: A Survivor's   
OL,16,FTale depicts how the author's parents  
OL,17,Fsurvived during the Holocaust.         
OL,19,FAuthor Art Spiegelman said he was      
OL,20,F"baffled" by the decision.             
